executive_summary.text: Overall status is Tripwire / Watch. Across the dashboard: 5 healthy, 3 tripwire, 0 stress. Biggest YoY moves: Revolving Consumer Credit (Δ 1y: +31594B (+2.4%)); Initial Jobless Claims (Δ 1y: -9000K (-4.2%)); Job Openings (Δ 1y: -0.97M (-12.9%)).

kpis.title: Card 30+ Delinquency
kpis.subtitle: FRED: DRCCLACBS (%, quarterly)
kpis.definition: Share of credit-card balances that are at least 30 days past due — an early consumer stress signal.
kpis.why: Rising delinquency is an early sign households are being squeezed.

kpis.title: Net Charge-off Rate
kpis.subtitle: FRED: CORCCACBS (%, quarterly)
kpis.definition: Portion of card loans written off as uncollectible — tends to lag delinquencies but confirms credit deterioration.
kpis.why: Charge-offs typically lag delinquencies but confirm deterioration.

kpis.title: Debt Service Burden
kpis.subtitle: FRED: TDSP (%, quarterly)
kpis.definition: Household debt payments as a percent of disposable personal income — a ‘squeeze’ measure that can rise even before delinquencies spike.
kpis.why: Higher debt service leaves less buffer to absorb shocks.

kpis.title: Mortgage 30+ Delinquency
kpis.subtitle: FRED: DRSFRMACBS (%, quarterly)
kpis.definition: Share of residential mortgages 30+ days delinquent (all commercial banks).
kpis.why: Mortgage delinquencies can jump in downturns and housing stress episodes.

kpis.title: Revolving Consumer Credit
kpis.subtitle: FRED: REVOLSL ($B, monthly)
kpis.definition: Total revolving consumer credit outstanding (primarily credit cards).
kpis.why: Rapid growth can signal households leaning on credit.

kpis.title: Job Openings
kpis.subtitle: FRED: JTSJOL (millions, monthly)
kpis.definition: Job openings (JOLTS). Proxy for labor demand.
kpis.why: Falling openings often precede labor market cooling.

kpis.title: Unemployment Rate
kpis.subtitle: FRED: UNRATE (%, monthly)
kpis.why: Rising unemployment tends to worsen credit performance.

kpis.title: Initial Jobless Claims
kpis.subtitle: FRED: ICSA (thousands, weekly)
kpis.definition: Weekly initial claims for unemployment insurance.
kpis.why: Claims are a fast-turn labor stress signal; spikes can precede higher unemployment.
